value.0: [The man looks engrossed in his work.]
[The man looks at you sideways a moment from his terminal] Busy here, what is it?

Aha! [He stops what he was doing and turns to give you his full attention] Good! I was beginning to wonder if she'd ever get off her arse and send me the help I requested! Seems it's not just the reception droid having issues, all my miners are down! If you could get down into the mine there, and bring me back ten pieces of Veldrite ore, I'd be most grateful!

Ah, well, that's a bit of a funny story. [He chuckles for a moment]

We had a bit of a... mess up with our droids down in the maintenance area.

Let's just say a minor firmware upgrade on our droids may - or may not - have turned them into homicidal killing machines. Needless to say, our team isn't cut out for fighting and security is busy dealing with other problems down there.
You'd have to talk to Halron - he's the security agent in charge. He'll have more info about those problems. For now, though, I need the Veldrite. Will you help me out?

Good, good. Here. [He hands you an old, decrepit resource harvester] You can have ol' reliable. She's on her last leg but it should get you started.

Talk to Darryn Bento if you need another harvester. He can be found at the northern end of this floor.
Aha, you're back! Did you get me the ten pieces of Veldrite ore, like I asked?

Excellent! And here's your work receipt! [He hands you over a piece of paper] 

If you need something else to do, I have another task for you. Just let me know if you're interested.
Ready for more work?
More harvesting, of course! I need you to head down and grab some more Veldite for me.
This is an engineering department. We're always in need of additional resources! Now then, head down and get more Veldite for me. But this time I want you to refine it first.

Use the refinery over there. [He motions toward the refineries at opposite ends of the large device].

You need to power the refinery with a Power Core. Talk to Darryn Beto at the north end of the facility if you need one. Once it's powered simply drop the ore inside to start refining it.

Bring the refined metal to me and I'll let you have one of these mods the boys cooked up in R&D.
Got that refined Veldite ready for me?
Remember - harvest the ore, use the refinery, place a power core inside, and then put the ore in to refine it. If you need a power core, Darryn at the north end of the facility will sell one to you.

[He inspects the metal] Not the highest quality refining job I've seen but it'll do for now. Here, pick one of these mods the R&D department constructed. It's the least I can do for you, considering you've saved my job.
Appreciate the help. Feel free to use those refineries any time you'd like.
Sorry, I'll leave you to it.
Selan sent me. She said you might need some help with the mining operation here?
Mining? Do I look like a grunt to you? Find someone else!
Why don't you do it yourself?
On second thought, I'm not interested anymore.
What do you mean?
What other problems?
[Nods] Alright. I'll see you when I've got the ore.
Thanks. I'll be back soon.
I'm still working on it.
Yes. [Hand over ore]
Thanks.
Not right now.
That depends. What do you need?
Again? What happened to the ore I just gave you?
How do I refine the ore?
All right. I'll do it.
Not yet. Still working on it.
Got it. Thanks.
Yes. [Hand over the refined Veldite]
I'll be back.
Yeah, no problem. Let's see those mods. [Select reward]
